<h3 dir="auto">Motivation</h3>
<p dir="auto">It is helpful for other developers to know that the user can move their mouse around during the process of "clicking" an element. Developers can also take advantage of this functionality since the click event will automatically trigger on the shared parent of the starting and ending elements. This could also alleviate any confusion developers might have if click events are triggering on their webpage when they don't think they should be.</p>]]></content>
